17/11/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- The government held an emergency session Wednesday (16 November) on the latest developments in southeastern Turkey.
The meeting coincided with reports of new clashes between police and local Kurd protestors in the Hakkari province's regional centre.
At least four people were reported killed and 15 injured in the unrest.
Prime Minister Recep Tayiip Erdogan is calling for restraint.
(Anadolu Agency, TurkishPress.com - 16/11/05)
